<div class='row'>
  <div class='col-sm-8'>
    <h1>EULA Automated Analysis Tool</h1>
    <br/>
    <form id='url-form'>
      <div class='form-group'>
        <label for='url'>URL to EULA</label>
        <div class='input-group'>
          <input class='form-control' name='url' type='url' placeholder='http://mywebsite.com/eula' required>
          <span class="input-group-btn">
            {{#link-to 'processing.eula' class='btn btn-success inline-go-btn'}}
              GO
            {{/link-to}}
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <br/>
      <p>
        <b>This Is a Link To:</b>
      </p>
      <div class='radio'>
        <label>
          <input type='radio' name='url_type' value='eula'/>
          A EULA
        </label>
      </div>
      <div class='radio'>
        <label>
          <input type='radio' name='url_type' value='eula'/>
          Home Page
        </label>
      </div>
    </form>
    <br/>
    <div class='row'>
      <div class='col-xs-4 col-sm-5'>
        <hr/>
      </div>
      <div class='col-xs-4 col-sm-2 text-center'>
        <span class='text-divider'>OR</span>
      </div>
      <div class='col-xs-4 col-sm-5'>
        <hr/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <br/>
    <form id='upload-form'>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for='file'>Upload a EULA</label>
        <input type='file' name='file' required>
      </div>
      <div>
        {{#link-to 'processing.eula' class='btn btn-success pull-right'}}
          Upload File
        {{/link-to}}
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
  <div class='col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-1 how-to-use'>
    <h4 class='text-center'>How to Use This Tool</h4>
    <br/>
    <p>The first option allows you to specify an online link. This can either be a link to the home page of the site you wish to analyze or the EULA itself.</p>
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <p>The 2nd option allows you to upload a local EULA in a pdf, doc, docx, or txt file. Your document will be analyzed but not remain on the server.</p>
  </div>
</div>
